50|$|Desmos chinensis is a {{flowering}} plant of the custard-apple family, Annonaceae. The yellowish-green flowers {{are similar to}} the <b>Ylang-ylang</b> flowers, therefore this plant is sometimes known as dwarf <b>ylang-ylang.</b> Their smell, however, is much less strong and is only felt in the morning. By midday it has mostly faded away.|$|E
50|$|The chief export {{crops are}} vanilla, cloves, <b>ylang-ylang,</b> and copra. The Comoros, {{including}} Mayotte, {{account for about}} 80% of world production of <b>ylang-ylang</b> essence, which is used in some perfumes. Marketed exports in 2004 included 44 tons of dried vanilla, valued at nearly $18.8 million, or 47% of agricultural exports.|$|E
